        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 4:00PM MDT by NWS Salt Lake City UT</headline>
        <description>At 359 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southwest of Cedar City. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kanarraville and Hamilton Fort.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 15 between mile markers 43 and 55.
Utah Route 56 between mile markers 47 and 53.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
